TITLE: Using ctx.runMutation for Partial Rollback (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a valid use case for ctx.runMutation within a mutation to achieve partial rollback on error. It shows how to handle errors while preserving some operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/get-convex/convex-backend/blob/main/npm-packages/docs/docs/understanding/best-practices/best-practices.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const sendMessage = mutation(
  async (ctx, { conversationId, text }) => {
    const messageId = await ctx.db.insert("messages", {
      conversationId,
      text,
    });

    try {
      await ctx.runMutation(async (txCtx) => {
        await sendPushNotification(txCtx, { conversationId, text });
      });
    } catch (error) {
      console.error("Failed to send push notification", error);
      // The message is still inserted even if the notification fails
    }

    return messageId;
  }
);
```

