TITLE: Updating Typing Status with useEffect
DESCRIPTION: A useEffect hook that updates the user's typing status based on message text changes. It sets typing to true when text is present, and reverts to false after 1 second of inactivity or immediately when text is empty.
SOURCE: https://github.com/get-convex/convex-backend/blob/main/npm-packages/demos/presence-typing-indicator/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
useEffect(() => {
  if (newMessageText.length === 0) {
    updateMyPresence({ typing: false });
    return;
  }
  updateMyPresence({ typing: true });
  const timer = setTimeout(() => updateMyPresence({ typing: false }), 1000);
  return () => clearTimeout(timer);
}, [updateMyPresence, newMessageText]);
```

