TITLE: Defining a Convex Mutation Function in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating a mutation function that accepts string arguments. It demonstrates how to validate arguments, write to the database by inserting a new document, and return the created document.
SOURCE: https://github.com/get-convex/convex-backend/blob/main/npm-packages/private-demos/nextjs-app-router-snippets/convex/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

